Ive had a user request that when employees/other are disabled, that instead of their userid being shown, that their names be shown instead.  This would still retain the red background indicating their non-availability but would preserve useful context of comments etc.

For us this would work, because we when employees/other leave the company, their account is simply disabled.  In our case, the user data is still there.  It seems plausible to attempt a username lookup, and if successful, use the username, and if not, fallback to userid.

