The HTTP retrieval service offers an InputStream back for any HTTP request. What many clients do is pipe the input stream straight into a DocumentBuilder or some other memory store, quickly leading to memory exhaustion if the data is large or the requests are frequent.

As well as providing a maximum size (which it already does), the service should be able to return InputStreams backed by responses that have been cached on disk.

